values:
Hey gang, 

That was the last chapter of Lullabies I ever wrote. I had several story arcs planned out, and of course, an endless supply of musical numbers. Maybe this year I'll write some more--- it's a good stress reliever for me, and you all seem to enjoy it. Stay tuned, my lieblings. Just check back every once in a while, see if anything pops up. As Denethor would say: same funky time, same funky channel. 

In the meantime, may the road rise up to meet you, may the wind always be at your back, and until we meet again, may God hold you in the palm of His hand.

There's no business like show business. 

~ Phantom

I just wanted to tell you all...

I'M GOING TO NEW YORK UNIVERSITY!!!

That's right, lieblings! In NINE months, I'm going to be LIVING in NEW YORK CITY, attending the TISCH SCHOOL OF THE ARTS as a member of the DRAMATIC WRITING PROGRAM. FOR REAL!!!! I'M GOING TO NEW YORK CITYYYYYYYY!!!!!!

I really wanted to thank all of you guys for your support through the years. If it hadn't been for you guys, I might have never seriously considered becoming a writer. All of your reviews, your compliments and praise, your encouragement --- man, the encouragement --- really gave me more of a boost than you can even imagine. I give you all a lot of credit for my success. I couldn't have gotten anywhere without a support group, my very own personal cheer squad.

Thank you all so much.

I MADE IT!!! I'M IN!!!! I'M GOING TO NEW YORK CITYYYYYY!!!!

-

All right, much love for my little lieblings. Lullabies will begin posting in about a week. I'm on vacation, and Lullabies is sitting at home on my hard drive being lonely. It misses its fans. 

Also, be glad that, unlike me, you did NOT have to perform the play A Thousand Cranes. If I never see another origami crane again, it'll be too soon. I made two hundred paper cranes, guys. TWO HUNDRED. And the play sucked. :P

Anyway. I'm going to try and figure out how to format the journal so you see the posts in reverse ordering of posting. That way, people don't have to go backwards to start at the beginning of the story, savvy? I'll get it done. 

Soon, my darlings! Soon!

-

Um, yes. Our backyard was struck by lightning. I'm not even kidding! And our computers got fried. Thus, you're going to have to wait a bit for the first installment of Lullabies. I'll post as soon as possible, I promise. 

~ Phantom

Meine dammen und herren, madames et messieurs, ladies and gentlemen...

Willkommen, bienvenue, welcome
Fremde, etrange, stranger
Glucklich se sehen, je suis enchante, happy to see you
Bleibe, reste, stay
Willkommen, bienvenue, welcome
Im Lullabies, au Lullabies, to Lullabies!

AS PROMISED!! Lullabies of Broadway is now online. I'll be posting one chapter at a time over a span of... I don't know. A while. Feel free to leave reviews by commenting on the entry. 

I love you all. 

Please enjoy...

*drumroll, please!!*

THE LULLABIES OF BROADWAY!!

~ Phantom
